5 Graphs
Graphs can be drawn in Tikz using nodes and edges. It can also be drawn (statically) using \usetikzlibrary{graphs} . For dynamic (automatic) placements of nodes use \setikzlibrary{graphdrawing}. Graphviz (.dot) can be used for quick layouts and is covered in a separate section.

5.1 Method1: nodes and edges
\begin{tikzpicture}
[every node/.style={draw, circle}]
{
\node (A) at (0,0) {A}; 
\node (B) at (2,0) {B};
\node (D) at (4,0) {D};
\node (C) at (2,-2) {C};
\draw (A) edge[-&gt;] node[draw=none, above]{1} (B);
\draw (B) edge[-&gt;] node[draw=none, above]{1} (D);
\draw (A) edge[-&gt;] node[draw=none, below]{2} (C);
\draw (C) edge[-&gt;] node[draw=none, below]{3} (D);
\end{tikzpicture}



5.2 Method2: usetikzlibrary{graphs}
\usetikzlibrary{graphs}

\begin{tikzpicture}
[n/.style={draw, circle}]
\node[n] (A) at (0,0) {A}; 
\node[n] (B) at (2,0) {B};
\node[n] (D) at (4,0) {D};
\node[n] (C) at (2,-2) {C};

\graph {
(A) -&gt;[edge label=1] (B);
(A) -&gt;[edge label=2, swap] (C);
(C) -&gt;[edge label=3, swap] (D);
(B) -&gt;[edge label=1] (D);
}
\end{tikzpicture}




5.3 graphs library: Another example
\usetikzlibrary{graphs, graphs.standard, quotes}
   % quotes library is for the [""] edges
\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance = {4cm and 3cm}, v/.style = {draw, circle}]
  \graph[nodes={circle, draw}, grow right=4cm, branch down=3cm]{
    A -- ["1"] C -- ["3"] E,
    B -- ["1",swap] D -- ["4",swap] F,
    B -- ["2"] A,
    C -- ["2"] {D,B},
    D -- ["3",swap] E -- ["1"] F
  };
\end{tikzpicture}
